&lt;p&gt;Miguel Cabrera of the Detroit Tigers is entering this season with career totals of &lt;strong&gt;2,866 hits&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;487 home runs&lt;/strong&gt; - so he is within reach of BOTH those marks this season, and his season averages are quite comfortably above what he needs to reach them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But here’s the more incredible thing…none, not a single one, of those six players in the 3000/500 club achieved both those milestones in the &lt;strong&gt;SAME&lt;/strong&gt; season…&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Miggy, make some history this year!&lt;/p&gt;
